uniol.apt.adt.subgraph

Class SubGraph<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uniol.apt.adt.extension.Extensible
      • uniol.apt.adt.subgraph.SubGraph<G,E,N>
  • Type Parameters:
    G - The type of the graph of which we are a subgraph.
    E - The type of edges of the graph of which we are a subgraph.
    N - The type of nodes of the graph of which we are a subgraph.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IExtensible, IGraph<SubGraph<G,E,N>,SubEdge<G,E,N>,SubNode<G,E,N>>

    public class SubGraph<G extends IGraph<G,E,N>,E extends IEdge<G,E,N>,N extends INode<G,E,N>>
extends Extensible
implements IGraph<SubGraph<G,E,N>,SubEdge<G,E,N>,SubNode<G,E,N>>
    A subgraph represents a part of another graph and is defined by a set of nodes of that graph. The subgraph contains exactly that set of nodes and all edges between this nodes. Note that this graph has to create wrappers around the nodes and edges of the original graph. Use SubEdge.getOriginalEdge() and SubNode.getOriginalNode() to get the edge respectively node of the original graph that is represented by such a wrapper object.
    Author:
    Uli Schlachter
